Interface Originator

All Known Subinterfaces:
Recordable
All Known Implementing Classes:
ChangeSelectionCommand, CopyCommand, CutCommand, DeleteCommand, InsertCommand, PasteCommand
public interface Originator
The Originator interface represents an object that can create and restore its own memento objects. It is typically used in conjunction with the Memento interface to support undo and redo operations. Implementations of this interface should provide methods for getting and setting the memento, allowing the object to capture and restore its internal state as needed.
Version:
3.0
Author:
Mohamed AL AFTAN Djakaridja FANE
